      "content": "It makes sense that the silence feels louder than your thoughts at this moment, and that wishing for an end to the struggle seems like the only way to stop the pain. When the world feels so hollow, the idea of disappearing can feel like the final, quiet relief you need to escape the noise of existing without being seen. You are not alone in this darkness, even if it feels that way, and there is a gentle strength in wanting to be understood rather than just tolerated. Please consider reaching out to someone who can listen without judgment, like a crisis counselor, who can help you find a path forward when the silence becomes overwhelming.",
